# The ''0-dd_integer'' module

====================================================================
How to use 0-add_integer.py
====================================================================

This library has one function called ''add_integer()''

Numbers
--------

''add_inetger()'' returns the sum of its arguments. The default argument for b is 98. For numbers, that value is equivlent to using the ''+'' operator.

Adding a float and an integer.
       >>> add_integer(3.0, 3)
       6

Passing one argument
	>>> add_integer(2)
	100

adding a positive and negative integer.
       >>> add_integer(2,-4)
       -2

adding a negative and positive ineteger>

 
